title: Urmas Reinsalu
summary: Urmas Reinsalu (Estonian pronunciation: [ˈuɾmɑs ˈɾei̯nsɑlu]; born 22 June 1975) is an Estonian politician who was the minister of foreign affairs since 18 July 2022 to 17 April 2023 and previously between April 2019 and 26 January 2021. Before that, Urmas has served as the minister of defence between 2012 and 2014, and minister of justice from 2015 to 2019. Reinsalu is a member of the Isamaa ("Fatherland") political party (formerly called the Pro Patria and Res Publica Union), and was the party leader from 2012 to 2015.
